article.description: — DeVante’ Jones had 24 points and 14 rebounds as Coastal Carolina extended its home win streak to seven games, defeating Georgia State 81-69 on Friday night.
article.headline: Jones leads Coastal Carolina over Georgia St. 81-69
article.linkText: Jones leads Coastal Carolina over Georgia St. 81-69
article.story: CONWAY, S.C. -- — DeVante’ Jones had 24 points and 14 rebounds as Coastal Carolina extended its home win streak to seven games, defeating Georgia State 81-69 on Friday night. Deanthony Tipler added 22 points for the Chanticleers. Essam Mostafa had 15 points and 16 rebounds for Coastal Carolina (7-1, 1-0 Sun Belt Conference). He also committed seven turnovers. Ebrima Dibba added 15 points. Justin Roberts had 14 points for the Panthers (6-2, 0-1), whose four-game winning streak came to an end. Kane Williams added 12 points. Corey Allen had 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
